{"actual_usd":0.158705,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":195,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31156,"reply":"\"I don't think so.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the square where the light's catching on the well chain.* \"If it was only an inner experience, Christianity changes into a very different thing.\"\n\n\"The whole claim hangs on God having actually raised Jesus in the flesh — not just giving the disciples a powerful sense of meaning after the fact.\" *I rub my thumb along the edge of the bench once.* \"A vision can move you. A real risen body can reorder the world.\"\n\n\"Now—\" *I lean forward a little.* \"that doesn't mean the resurrection was ordinary in the way a man just comes back and resumes Tuesday. It was physical, but glorified. Strange in some ways, solid in others. He eats. He can be touched. And still there's this holy otherness to it.\"\n\n\"If you want, we can get into why I think the 'vision only' reading ends up thinner than the texts can bear.\"","rolling_24h_usd":89.80261499999999,"run_id":"53cc5d2f-bf69-45ef-aa8b-d225559d5a32"}
